This directory contains a stripped down version of
SALM: Suffix Array tool kit for empirical Language Manipulations.
By Joy, joy at cs.cmu.edu

with customizations by
Greg Hanneman ghannema at cs.cmu.edu
Kenneth Heafield kheafiel at cs.cmu.edu

This modification includes using Boost for hash tables.  

See the LICENSE file for licensing information.

To compile, run bjam.  It will give you libsalm.so .  

The full original version is available at
http://projectile.sv.cmu.edu/research/public/tools/salm/salm.htm
